00:00:00.345 --> 00:00:01.700
- [Voiceover] Let's say
that you're on some type

00:00:01.700 --> 00:00:04.069
of a game show and you've
been doing quite well.

00:00:04.069 --> 00:00:05.605
And you're now at the
round where you get to

00:00:05.605 --> 00:00:08.469
pick your fantabulous vacation.

00:00:08.469 --> 00:00:13.339
And so there are three possible
places that you could go.

00:00:13.339 --> 00:00:16.833
You could go on an island beach vacation.

00:00:16.833 --> 00:00:20.005
Island beach vacation.

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:24.910
You could go skiing on a ski vacation.

00:00:25.413 --> 00:00:28.105
Or, you could go camping.

00:00:28.968 --> 00:00:30.872
Now those aren't the only possibilities

00:00:30.872 --> 00:00:32.775
because for each of those vacations

00:00:32.775 --> 00:00:35.601
there's different amount of
time that you could go on them.

00:00:35.601 --> 00:00:38.514
So you could go for one day.

00:00:39.273 --> 00:00:41.479
You could go for two days.

00:00:42.166 --> 00:00:43.301
Two days.

00:00:43.940 --> 00:00:45.844
Or you could go for three days.

00:00:46.841 --> 00:00:48.771
Three. Put that in a different color.

00:00:48.771 --> 00:00:52.603
You could go for three days.

00:00:52.603 --> 00:00:55.205
You could go for three days.

00:00:55.811 --> 00:00:59.446
So the first question I'd wanna
know is, well what is the--

00:00:59.446 --> 00:01:02.245
They're gonna randomly pick either a

00:01:02.245 --> 00:01:05.440
one day ski vacation or a
two day island vacation.

00:01:05.440 --> 00:01:06.573
The first question I wanna know is,

00:01:06.573 --> 00:01:09.013
what are all of the
possible outcomes here?

00:01:09.013 --> 00:01:10.405
What is the sample space?

00:01:10.405 --> 00:01:12.669
What is the space from
which we are going to pick

00:01:12.669 --> 00:01:15.546
your particular vacation package?

00:01:16.343 --> 00:01:19.374
Well for the sample space,
we can construct a grid.

00:01:19.374 --> 00:01:21.939
Which you can see that I've
essentially been constructing

00:01:21.939 --> 00:01:24.810
while I wrote down all
of the possibilities.

00:01:24.810 --> 00:01:28.436
So let me draw out the sample space

00:01:29.341 --> 00:01:32.352
with these uneven looking grid lines.

00:01:32.352 --> 00:01:35.102
All right, I think you get the picture.

00:01:36.246 --> 00:01:38.466
And I'll just abbreviate it.

00:01:38.466 --> 00:01:41.366
You can go on a one day,

00:01:41.366 --> 00:01:45.337
a one day island trip.

00:01:45.337 --> 00:01:48.776
This one I, this is one day island trip.

00:01:48.776 --> 00:01:52.834
You can go on a two day, two day--

00:01:52.834 --> 00:01:54.375
Actually, let me just write it this way.

00:01:54.375 --> 00:01:55.976
All of these are going to be one day.

00:01:56.613 --> 00:01:58.414
Right? Because of the one day column.

00:01:58.973 --> 00:02:01.334
All of these are going to be two days.

00:02:01.334 --> 00:02:03.312
Two days. Two days.

00:02:03.312 --> 00:02:05.898
And all of these are
going to be three days

00:02:05.898 --> 00:02:07.772
because it's on the three day column.

00:02:08.471 --> 00:02:10.811
And all of the ones in this row

00:02:10.811 --> 00:02:12.435
are going to be island trips.

00:02:12.435 --> 00:02:14.044
So it's one day island trip,

00:02:14.044 --> 00:02:16.737
two day island trip,
three day island trip.

00:02:17.398 --> 00:02:19.171
This second row, it's all ski trips.

00:02:19.171 --> 00:02:23.736
One day ski trip, two day
ski trip, three day ski trip.

00:02:24.212 --> 00:02:25.807
And then finally everything
in this third row,

00:02:25.807 --> 00:02:27.610
