00:02:34.081 --> 00:02:35.938
the sample space right over here.

00:02:35.938 --> 00:02:38.077
You see that there's one,
two, three, four, five,

00:02:38.077 --> 00:02:40.482
six, seven, eight, nine outcomes.

00:02:40.482 --> 00:02:42.146
And let's say that each of these outcomes

00:02:42.146 --> 00:02:43.100
are on a little piece of paper

00:02:43.100 --> 00:02:44.969
and they put it in a
barrel and they roll it up.

00:02:44.969 --> 00:02:46.702
And for our purposes we can assume

00:02:46.702 --> 00:02:49.808
that they are all equally likely outcomes.

00:02:49.808 --> 00:02:53.036
So we're gonna assume
equally likely outcomes.

00:02:53.036 --> 00:02:55.375
So if we do assume
equally likely outcomes,

00:02:55.375 --> 00:02:56.579
we can figure out a probability.

00:02:56.579 --> 00:02:59.410
Maybe you live in someplace that's cold

00:02:59.410 --> 00:03:01.974
and you're really not in
the mood to go skiing.

00:03:01.974 --> 00:03:03.542
In fact, you'd like to spend several days

00:03:03.542 --> 00:03:05.543
away from the snow.

00:03:05.543 --> 00:03:07.046
So let's ask ourselves a question.

00:03:07.642 --> 00:03:11.004
What is the probability

00:03:11.004 --> 00:03:12.939
that you're going to win something

00:03:12.939 --> 00:03:17.170
at least two days

00:03:17.170 --> 00:03:19.713
on a vacation without snow.

00:03:19.713 --> 00:03:24.109
Two days on vacation

00:03:24.109 --> 00:03:27.744
without snow.

00:03:27.744 --> 00:03:31.379
You're gonna randomly pick
one of these nine outcomes.

00:03:31.379 --> 00:03:34.642
What's the probability that
it's going to be at least--

00:03:34.642 --> 00:03:35.836
It's gonna give you a
vacation that gives you

00:03:35.836 --> 00:03:38.739
at least two days without snow.

00:03:39.644 --> 00:03:41.500
Well, let's just think
a little bit about it.

00:03:41.500 --> 00:03:42.802
We know the sample space

00:03:42.802 --> 00:03:44.903
and we know each of the
outcomes are equally likely.

00:03:44.903 --> 00:03:47.943
There are nine equal outcomes here.

00:03:47.943 --> 00:03:49.172
So let's write that down.

00:03:49.172 --> 00:03:51.367
We got nine equal outcomes.

00:03:52.268 --> 00:03:56.075
Now how many of the outcomes satisfy this?

00:03:56.075 --> 00:03:58.637
This event, this constraint.

00:03:58.637 --> 00:04:01.438
At least 2 days of vacation--

00:04:01.438 --> 00:04:03.233
Let me write this.

00:04:03.233 --> 00:04:05.307
Two days.

00:04:06.811 --> 00:04:07.572
Without snow.

00:04:07.572 --> 00:04:09.301
Whether it falls or
touching it or whatever.

00:04:09.301 --> 00:04:11.007
So you're essentially avoiding skiing.

00:04:11.007 --> 00:04:13.701
You want at least two days on
something other than skiing.

00:04:13.701 --> 00:04:14.707
And we're assuming you're
not gonna go camping

00:04:14.707 --> 00:04:16.267
in some type of alpine.

00:04:16.267 --> 00:04:18.179
You're camping in some place that's warm.

00:04:18.746 --> 00:04:20.113
Well, let's think about these outcomes.

00:04:20.572 --> 00:04:23.247
So this one is no snow
but it's only one day.

00:04:23.876 --> 00:04:28.435
This is two days without snow
so we can circle that one.

00:04:28.435 --> 00:04:32.071
This is three days without
snow so we can circle that one.

00:04:32.071 --> 00:04:33.737
All of these have snow.

00:04:34.269 --> 00:04:36.847
This is one day without snow
so we're not gonna do this one.

00:04:36.847 --> 00:04:38.811
This is two days without snow

00:04:38.811 --> 00:04:41.333
and this is three days without snow.

00:04:41.944 --> 00:04:43.713
And so four of the equally

00:04:43.713 --> 00:04:46.346
likely outcomes satisfy this constraint.

00:04:46.939 --> 00:04:49.880
So you have a 4/9 probability

00:04:49.880 --> 00:04:52.568
of getting a vacation

00:04:52.568 --> 00:04:56.876
that keeps you away from
snow for at least two days.

00:04:56.876 --> 00:04:59.043
Hopefully you found that fun
and useful for the next time

00:04:59.043 --> 00:05:01.413
that you are some type
of strange game show.

